xwayland: don't crash when the Wayland output geometry is (transiently) invalid

SYMPTOM
  With libxcvt >= 0.1.3 (git "0.1.3+8"), Xwayland dies deterministically:
      (EE) Failed to allocate memory for list of RR modes      (FatalError)
  and, before the cvt.c NULL guard, as:
      (EE) Segmentation fault at address 0x10                  (NULL ->dot_clock)
  KWin then gives up: "Stopping Xwayland ... crashed 4 times over 10 minutes".
  Reverting libxcvt to <= 0.1.3+3 hides the problem.

ROOT CAUSE (audited against libxcvt upstream commits)
  Between libxcvt 0.1.3+3 and 0.1.3+8, MR!22 added input validation to
  libxcvt_gen_mode_info():
      23c30d4 "Avoid potential division by zero"   (rejects hdisplay/vdisplay <= 0,
                                                     vfield_rate/hperiod <= 0, htotal/vtotal == 0)
      410ef8f "Add bounds checking..."             (rejects dimension > 1048576, vrefresh > 10000)
      0f69a87 "Avoid integer overflow in uint16_t assignments"
  A differential test of the OLD vs NEW libxcvt over all 1120 realistic
  (resolution x refresh x reduced) combinations an HP X27q / KWin can present
  shows ZERO divergence: every real mode is generated identically. The NEW code
  only returns NULL for DEGENERATE input - hdisplay <= 0 or vdisplay <= 0
  (and absurd > 1048576 / > 10000 Hz). For such input the OLD libxcvt returned a
  GARBAGE mode instead (vrefresh = -nan, dot_clock = 0, or hdisplay wrapped to
  4294967288 via int->unsigned overflow) - i.e. it never should have "worked";
  the div-by-zero / overflow it performed was undefined behaviour.

  So this is a LATENT XWAYLAND bug newly EXPOSED by a CORRECT libxcvt hardening:
  Xwayland feeds xwl_output->{width,height} straight into libxcvt from
  apply_output_change() on every wl_output/xdg_output "done" event, and that
  geometry is transiently 0 during early output setup, hotplug, or VRR /
  adaptive-sync mode-flapping (as on the X27q). Xwayland then dereferenced /
  FatalError'd on the NULL. libxcvt is behaving correctly; Xwayland is at fault.

FIX (Xwayland only - correct, minimal, and robust against any libxcvt)
  1) hw/xwayland/xwayland-cvt.c
     xwayland_modeinfo_from_cvt() returns Bool and xwayland_cvt() returns NULL
     when libxcvt_gen_mode_info() fails, instead of dereferencing NULL
     (defense in depth; kills the SIGSEGV-at-0x10 form).
  2) hw/xwayland/xwayland-output.c
     - apply_output_change(): only rebuild the RandR mode list when
       mode_width > 0 && mode_height > 0. On invalid size the mode update is
       deferred (a valid "done" always follows) while ALL the surrounding
       bookkeeping - screen-size update, output_list insertion and the
       expecting_event decrement - still runs, so startup/hotplug completes
       normally. RRCrtcNotify() with a NULL mode is explicitly supported by the
       RandR core, so the output simply carries no mode until a valid size
       arrives. No bogus/fallback mode is fabricated and libxcvt is not even
       called with bad input (one fewer allocation on the flap path).
     - output_get_rr_modes(): a rejected optional fake/emulated CVT mode is now
       skipped instead of triggering FatalError(); the real mode is already in
       rr_modes[0]. FatalError() remains only for a genuine primary allocation
       failure (its original intent).

  No libxcvt change is required or desirable: its new validation is correct and
  breaks no real mode. This Xwayland fix also protects users running the distro
  libxcvt and any future stricter libxcvt.

